Package: VaccineValidateR
Type: Package
Title: Vaccine Validator for United States Childhood Immunization Schedules
Version: 0.0.1.0
Date: 2025-09-11
Author: Jeremy J Michel <michelj@chop.edu>
Maintainer: Jeremy J Michel <michelj@chop.edu>
License: BSD-2
Description: 
    VaccineValidateR provides tools to clean, standardize, and validate childhood immunization data 
    according to US ACIP recommendations and immunize.org guidance. The package allows mapping 
    local immunization codes to CVX codes, selecting immunizations of interest, and filtering data 
    for analysis. It supports evaluation of dose validity, series completion, and timing checks 
    for routine and catch-up childhood vaccines, including COVID-19, Influenza, Tetanus, HIB, 
    PCV, Polio, and other common antigens. The package facilitates reproducible and transparent 
    vaccine data validation workflows for research and clinical quality improvement.
